President Donald J. Trump and President Moon Jae-in of South Korea discussed the allied response to North Korea's claimed hydrogen bomb test. They agreed that North Korea's provocation poses a grave threat to the world and pledged to maximize pressure on the country. They also agreed to strengthen joint military capabilities and President Trump approved South Korea's initiative to lift restrictions on their missile payload capabilities. Additionally, President Trump gave conceptual approval for South Korea to purchase military weapons and equipment worth billions of dollars from the United States.